# pato Gram Output

Any `pato` subcommand that emits gram on stdout must pass that output through the shared
canonical formatter before writing it.

- Reuse the shared formatter helper from `crates/pato/src/commands/fmt.rs`.
- Do not let individual renderers invent their own whitespace, property ordering, or blank-line style.
- Apply this to diagnostics now and to future gram-producing commands such as `parse`, `rule`, and `check`.
- Add or update tests so gram-producing commands emit output that is already canonical when re-formatted.
